name: Sofia M.
title: Roots in the Garden
description: My portrait is surrounded by marigolds from my abuela's garden. Each flower is coded with randomized petals so no two are the same, just like my family's stories. The process of creating this was a journey of technical growth. Before Code/Art, I thought coding was just about getting a computer to do math, but I discovered that programming is actually a canvas. I can use variables, loops, and functions just like a traditional artist uses paint and brushes. For this project, I wanted to create something that truly represented who I am and where I come from. Translating my paper sketches into a coordinate plane in p5.js was challenging. I had to calculate exact x and y positions, understand how shapes overlap using z-indexing, and use trigonometry like sine and cosine to create natural, flowing movements. Incorporating interactivity was another major milestone. I wanted the viewer to feel like they were a part of my story, so I added event listeners for mouse movements and clicks, making the portrait feel alive and reactive. This artwork proves that technology and art are two sides of the same coin, and it tells my unique story.
